  "considerations": [
   {
    "heading": "Runways",
    "body": [
     "ILS and RNAV approach available on RWY 6. Circle-to-land approach RWY 24.",
     "High raising terrain north and northeast of the airport coupled with heavily congested GA traffic over REI (Redland Municipal Airport) can make operating into SBD difficult when conditions do not favor RWY 6",
     "REI is overflown while maneuvering to final for a circle-to-land approach to RWY 24.     50% of the aircraft over this airport are not equipped with a transponder or ADS-B, which means that identifying traffic and maintaining visual separation is a must for our crews.",
     "Special restrictions and minimums are in place for a circle-to-land approach to RWY 24 and can be found on our 10-7 “Company Information” charts on Jeppesen. Whenever a circle-to-land looks probable, we must consider the following:",
     "Circle “visual manuever” to RWY 24 is DAYLIGHT,  PIC only and contingent on operable HIRL, REIL and PAPI.",
     "Minimum ceiling is 2,000 feet AGL and minimum visibility is 5 SM."
    ]
   }
  ],
